<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-03-20T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-03-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="154" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 T 71/138: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                    Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-20T19:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">March 20,
                                        1919, 7 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received March 20, 3:25
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>1241. Following from Helsingfors from <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">Bullitt</persName>:</p>
                        <p>“Soviet Government has given explicit orders of which I have a copy for
                            the immediate release of <persName>Tredwell</persName> by the local
                            Soviet of Tashkent. Due to the breaking in telegraphic communication
                            between Moscow and Turkestan Soviet Government had not received
                            notification of the carrying out of these orders when I left. Unless
                                <persName>Tredwell</persName> prefers to go to Persia he will be
                            sent to Moscow and thence home via Friedland [<hi rend="italic">Finland
                                ?</hi>].”</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>